<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xml:lang="en"
      xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
      xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
      xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
      lang="en"
      metal:use-macro="context/main_template/macros/master">
  <body>
    <metal:main fill-slot="main">
      <tal:main-macro metal:define-macro="main">
        <div tal:define="programs view/getPrograms">
          This will be a basic first-step application form, a query param is used so the selection of which program
          can be pre-populated and APPLY NOW button can do so directly.  When it is POSTED, participant object will be created and the program-specific
          questions and such can be copied over before applicant ever sees confusing fields about potential questions.
          <br><br><form action="${portal_url}/apply" method="post">
            First name:<br>
            <input type="text" name="firstname" required /><br>
            Last name:<br>
            <input type="text" name="lastname" required /><br>
            Email:<br>
            <input type="text" name="email" required /><br>
            <select name="programID" required>
              <option tal:repeat="program programs"
                      tal:attributes="value program/uid;
                                      selected program/selected"
                      tal:content="program/name" />

            </select><br><br>
            <input type="submit" value="Submit" />
          </form>
        </div>
      </tal:main-macro>
    </metal:main>
  </body>
</html>
